The problem seems to be that `sqrt` from `cmath` accepts only scalars, whereas you are trying to use it in a vectorized manner by providing it a 2-d array. One solution is to apply `cmath.sqrt` on each element of `t` and `g` by looping through them as follows:

    def ReE1(t,g):
        E1 = np.zeros(t.shape, dtype=&#39;complex&#39;)    
        for i in range(t.shape[0]):
            for j in range(t.shape[1]):
                E1[i][j]=eps+cmath.sqrt(t[i][j]**2-g[i][j]**2)
        return E1.real 
    
    def ReE2(t,g):
        E2 = np.zeros(t.shape, dtype=&#39;complex&#39;)    
        for i in range(t.shape[0]):
            for j in range(t.shape[1]):
                E2[i][j]=eps-cmath.sqrt(t[i][j]**2-g[i][j]**2)
        return E2.real 

